LinkSidebar
An extension for Mozilla Firefox.

View, search and test hyperlinks in a web page.
Perform group actions on multiple links like opening in tabs, copying link locations or testing to determine response times. Allows you to search/sort links and highlight their position on the webpage.

https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/linksidebar/

Build Instructions:

1. Download the Extension Developer extension (https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/extension-developer/) and choose the 'build extension' option.
2. Get the Firefox versions allowable for hosting on addons.mozilla.ord from this page: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/pages/appversions/ and update the install.rdf file with the latest tested versions.



